The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Four more join TCS board

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Mumbai, Sept. 6: Tata Consultancy Services (TCS), the countrys largest software services exporter, today included four whole-time executive directors on its board. 

 There are now 12 members on the board, including 6 independent directors.

 The four executive vice-presidents elevated to the board are N. Chandrasekaran, S. Mahalingam, S. Padmanabhan and P.A. Vandrevala.

 The board also appointed N. Chandrasekaran as the chief operating officer.

 S. Ramadorai, chief executive officer and managing director of TCS, said, Given the size of the companys business, the directors have decided to take four senior executives on the board of directors. 

 The newly appointed executive directors have a wealth of experience and have contributed significantly to the growth and success of TCS and will continue to play an important role in the companys future strategy, he said.

 TCS has six independent directors: Ron Sommer, former chairman of Deutsche Telekom; Clayton Christensen, a Harvard professor; Aman Mehta, former HSBC chief; Naresh Chandra, former cabinet secretary; V. Thyagarajan, head of Glaxo SmithKline Asia; and Laura Cha, a member of the executive council of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region. 




